				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The TE28F320 is a 2MiWx16bit 3V-only EEPROM. Could be interfaced to a Genesis by adding some voltage shifting ICs. Could be interfaced to a SNES by adding the voltage shifting ICs <em>and</em> either ignoring half the capacity or adding some multiplexers. Would be kinda pointless to interface to the NES because the NES requires extra and widely varying hardware to address more than 32 KiB of memory..<br /><br />BUT you can also buy new FLASH 'PROMs of the same dimensions, capacity, and voltage for only $1, so I don't see any point in buying an R4 for this purpose.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
